Turn your idea into a testable system

If you want breadcrumb → adoption to be real, make it observable:

1) Package the pattern
	•	PANTHEON_RUNTIME.md (core)
	•	/roles/*.md (role cards)
	•	/skills/*.md (task contracts)
	•	/examples/ (before/after on real tasks)

2) Add measurable hooks
	•	Use-cases: “Find 3 bugs in repo X,” “Refactor module Y,” “Generate spec Z”
	•	Metrics: time saved, defects found, pass rate, user preference
	•	A/B: Pantheon vs. baseline prompt

3) Make discovery easy
	•	Clear README + quick-start (copy/paste runnable)
	•	Minimal friction (one command / one prompt to try)
	•	Versioned releases + changelog

4) Track uptake
	•	Stars/forks, downloads, issues
	•	External mentions, forks with modifications
	•	Reproduced results by others

5) Close the loop
	•	Log failures and fixes
	•	Publish improvements
	•	Show consistent wins across tasks and models

